@node Installation "Installation"
@version 2.082
@toc Main
@Index AORM.Index/Index

    - INSTALLATION -

        Installing Amiga Online Reference Manual is very easy. There are
    four files to be installed. The main file is the AORM hypertext
    document, containing over 700k of data. Upon double-clicking the
    Install-AORM icon, you will be asked where you wish to place AORM.
    You will require approximately 800k of disk space or more.
        AmigaGuide is also used by AORM. This file is stored in your
    SYS:Utilities drawer. The AmigaGuide.library will be copied to your
    LIBS: directory, and requires 65k of disk space. After these files are
    installed, the installation is complete.

        If AmigaGuide is properly installed, you may use AORM simply by
    double clicking its icon. If you choose, you may use AORM from the
    floppy disk without installing it.


    - IF YOUR DISK IS DAMAGED -

        Return your damaged disk to us at:

            Area52 Customer Behavior Modifications Department
            107 River Park Drive
            Liverpool, New York 13090-2841

        All disks containing unreadable files will be replaced free of
    charge provided that the disk is an original Area52 disk. All
    customers are offered one free disk repair. We highly suggest all
    customers back-up their disks and store the original in a safe place.
    Additional damaged disk replacements are $2 to cover shipping and
    handling, as of June 1st, 1993, subject to change.

