@node Table "Table"
@version 2.085
@toc Main
@prev Rock
@next Float

    - Table -

            A Table is a large rectangular or circular device which is
        often used to support objects, or in most cases food, above the
        floor. Tables are also designed such that smaller table-like
        objects called "Chairs" may be placed around them. The purpose
        of a Chair is for humans to be seated in an upright position
        around the Table.
            Tables are also common in bar fights, used for special effects.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Rock "Rock"
@version 2.085
@toc Main
@prev Rock
@next Table

    - Rock -

            Before Tables existed, cavemen had to rely on other objects
        to support objects or food above the ground. These included but
        were not limited to large flat "Rocks". Rocks served their purpose
        well, since they were sturdy and did not move much. However, with
        the advent of modern Tables, the use of Rocks slowly diminished
        in the early Tablonian period, or "Age of the Tables". Tables were
        often stored on Rocks.
            Some enthusiastic cavemen attempted to store the larger Rocks
        on Tables, but failed miserably.

@endnode
+-----------------------------------------------------------------------------+


@node Float "Float"
@version 2.085
@toc Main
@prev Table
@next Float

    - Float -

            In the future, food and stuff will just Float around, so
        Tables and Rocks will no longer be necessary.

            For more information on Float, see your local Baskin Robbins.

@endnode
