@node Manual "Omega Off-line Severance Manual"
@version 2.085
@toc Main
@prev Manual
@next Manual

    16.54 What is the Omega Off-line Severance Manual?

            The OOSM is the highly acclaimed work of art designed to
        teach you how to use the fabulous Omega computer. Here is a
        list of included topics which I am going to type right now on
        this page that you are reading today:


                1. How to use AutoExec.Splatch files.

                2. How to list all the contents of a directory using
                   the **.?$*.BG..** wildcard.

                3. How to fit 360k on one 5.25" floppy disk!

                4. How to fit one 3.5" disk into one of those fake drive
                   bays that looks like it is a floppy drive but really
                   is only a faceplate with the openings blocked and
                   a fake button.

                5. How to move a mouse pointer jerkily, and how to plug
                   it into your SVGA port.

                6. Why all machines have 1 megabyte, but you only get to
                   use 640k.

                7. Why we use Itnel processors.

                8. Why WindowsNT 1.0 doesn't exist.

                9. Why WindowsNT 2.0 doesn't exist.

               10. Why OS/4 is coming out next.

@endnode
